reviews.review_text: Thank You Brother Bear I'll take a great sounding audience recording over a sterile soundboard any day. While boards can be great for hearing the technical accuracy of songs, to me they lack the energy that makes a Dead show a Dead show. This recording captures that energy and does it very well. The show? It's May, it's 1977, it's Hartford.......what do you think?
get the other aud recording The Jerry Moore recording of this show is far superior - unfortunately this one is unlistenable, at least for me, anyway.

Great Show! Wow. I've never heard Sugaree jam that much. It's so exciting. This is an incredible show. Oh, and I agree with the reviewer about how an audience tape can capture the energy of everyone. There are shows I saw in basketball arenas (like Rosemont or Oakland Coliseum) where the roaring of the music and the crowd made it feel like there was going to be an explosion. Some would say the acoustics were bad at those shows, but I loved it that way. In this case, distortion's a good thing.
what a great show yup - there is crowd noise, just like all the tapes once had. I love it!
